Anti-Aliasing Filter: An anti-aliasing filter is a low-pass filter placed before the DAQ input to remove high-frequency components that could cause aliasing when the signal is sampled by the DAQ. The filter's cutoff frequency should be slightly less than half the DAQ's sampling rate, as per the Nyquist theorem, to ensure accurate digital representation of the analog signal.

DAQ Input: This is the interface to the Data Acquisition system (DAQ) which digitizes the conditioned analog signal. The DAQ's specifications, including its maximum voltage level and whether it accepts single-ended or differential input, determine the final signal conditioning requirements not specified in this project.
